cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with generating textures of human bodies from a single image, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as 3D human body pose estimation and person re-identification. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graphics (GR) techniques such as rendering synthetic images with textures, which makes cs.GR a likely sub-category as well. The paper uses machine learning (ML) techniques such as end-to-end learning and maximizing similarity, which makes cs.MM and cs.LG likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper explores the possible utilization of the generated textures, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques such as image recognition and classification, making cs.AI a possible sub-category.
